## How each mandatory requirement is met

- **SQL injection** — every query uses `?` parameter placeholders (raw `sqlite3`, no string building).
- **Password hashing** — Argon2id via `argon2-cffi` (auto-salted), with rehash-on-login.
- **XSS** — Jinja2 autoescaping; paste text rendered escaped inside `<pre>`; strict CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline).
- **CSRF** — Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` enforces a token on every POST (create, delete, login, logout, register).
- **Access control / IDOR** — delete verifies `owner_id == session user` → non-owners get 403; paste IDs are 12-byte random tokens, not sequential.
- **Session cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (configurable); session cleared/rotated on login (fixation defense).
- **Security headers** — CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS on HTTPS.
- **Input validation** — server-side length/format (allow-list regex) checks; 2 MB body cap.
- **No leaked internals** — `debug=False`, custom 4xx/5xx pages, exceptions logged server-side only.
- **No hardcoded secrets** — `SECRET_KEY` read from env (ephemeral fallback with a warning so it still runs).

